Name:arbInt

Categories: Library

Function:
* `int arbInt( )`
* `int arbInt(int limit)`

Description: Return an arbitrary integer value. When the argument `limit` is given, the generated value is in the interval [0, `limit`].

Examples:
<screen>
import Integer;
arbInt()
arbInt()
arbInt()
</screen>

Benefits: <tt>arbInt</tt> is a convenient generator for pseudo-random integers.

